WEBVTT

00:00:34.722 --> 00:00:38.059
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

00:00:38.643 --> 00:00:41.062
Mi-sook, congrats on going back to work.

00:00:41.146 --> 00:00:42.605
Thank you.

00:00:42.689 --> 00:00:44.065
Good job, Bom.

00:00:44.149 --> 00:00:45.692
-I'll put in three candles.
-All right.

00:00:46.192 --> 00:00:47.569
-Wow.
-Ta-da.

00:00:47.652 --> 00:00:48.695
It opened.

00:00:54.117 --> 00:00:54.993
Hello.

00:00:55.076 --> 00:00:56.995
Welcome. Wait…

00:00:59.873 --> 00:01:01.624
Who are you people?

00:01:03.626 --> 00:01:04.502
I got a job.

00:01:05.378 --> 00:01:06.588
All thanks to you.

00:01:11.259 --> 00:01:12.468
Goodness me.

00:01:30.320 --> 00:01:32.488
What do you think you're doing?
Let go of her.

00:01:32.572 --> 00:01:34.115
-Damn it. Let go of me.
-Hold on.

00:01:34.198 --> 00:01:36.034
Keum-bo!

00:01:38.202 --> 00:01:39.370
What's going on here?

00:01:39.996 --> 00:01:42.248
-Just stop fighting it and come on.
-Let go!

00:01:42.332 --> 00:01:43.291
Who the hell are you?

00:01:43.958 --> 00:01:45.209
That's why

00:01:45.877 --> 00:01:48.880
you should've taught your daughter better.

00:01:49.547 --> 00:01:50.548
Take care of them.

00:01:50.632 --> 00:01:53.468
Jeez. Lady, just get back inside.

00:01:53.551 --> 00:01:54.761
Step aside already.

00:02:01.893 --> 00:02:03.811
-No!
-Who the hell are you?

00:02:05.063 --> 00:02:06.231
-Mi-sook.
-Damn it.

00:02:20.703 --> 00:02:21.829
Are you okay?

00:02:32.590 --> 00:02:34.676
Stop. That hurts.

00:02:35.843 --> 00:02:36.970
You.

00:02:47.605 --> 00:02:49.023
Keum-bo! Watch out!

00:02:53.820 --> 00:02:55.822
Go after my daughters…

00:02:57.407 --> 00:02:58.950
TAEKKYEON

00:02:59.033 --> 00:03:01.035
…and you'll end up in hell, mister.

00:03:03.329 --> 00:03:04.163
Honey!

00:03:57.300 --> 00:03:59.469
You bastard!

00:03:59.552 --> 00:04:01.971
Hey! Stop that!

00:04:03.473 --> 00:04:04.891
Stop that!

00:04:08.227 --> 00:04:09.228
Let's go.

00:04:11.731 --> 00:04:13.733
-Dad, are you okay?
-Yeah, I'm fine. Are you?

00:04:13.816 --> 00:04:14.776
Yeah.

00:04:16.819 --> 00:04:17.737
Are you okay, honey?

00:04:26.496 --> 00:04:29.540
EPISODE 15: NO MERCY

00:04:30.625 --> 00:04:33.294
I really think I might need an X-ray.

00:04:33.378 --> 00:04:35.588
I told you I was just there
to see my little sister.

00:04:35.671 --> 00:04:38.674
There he is!
Man, that scoundrel is rotten to the core.

00:04:38.758 --> 00:04:39.842
We're the victims here.

00:04:39.926 --> 00:04:41.677
-My heart is still racing!
-Stop hitting me!

00:04:41.761 --> 00:04:43.763
You thought you could
come after my daughter?

00:04:43.846 --> 00:04:45.306
You punk!

00:04:48.267 --> 00:04:50.353
What did your parents do
before opening the restaurant?

00:04:50.436 --> 00:04:52.355
Where did they first meet?

00:04:52.438 --> 00:04:54.232
I heard they met at a gym.

00:04:54.816 --> 00:04:57.485
He was a Taekkyeon master,
and she was Little Miss Martial Arts.

00:04:58.111 --> 00:04:59.153
I see.

00:05:01.406 --> 00:05:04.700
When did Go Bok-cheol team up with them?

00:05:05.451 --> 00:05:08.663
A while ago, Ms. Song asked
if my brother had been released.

00:05:08.746 --> 00:05:09.831
Those good-for-nothings.

00:05:11.124 --> 00:05:12.708
Bom, you must've been so scared.

00:05:14.335 --> 00:05:18.005
I was fine because
I had Auntie Nora by my side.

00:05:18.089 --> 00:05:20.633
We even called the police.

00:05:26.389 --> 00:05:29.100
I recognized the man
who dragged Ms. Hong away earlier.

00:05:31.394 --> 00:05:32.228
I've seen him before.

00:05:33.104 --> 00:05:35.106
When? Where did you see him?

00:05:37.108 --> 00:05:38.151
When I was ten…

00:05:40.194 --> 00:05:41.237
At my house.

00:05:49.912 --> 00:05:51.038
Where is the kid?

00:05:51.122 --> 00:05:53.291
-We don't know.
-We swear we don't!

00:05:54.542 --> 00:05:56.127
Where the hell is she?

00:05:56.210 --> 00:05:58.588
-I really don't know.
-Tell me where she is!

00:06:02.550 --> 00:06:05.136
-You'd better hide yourself well
-Where could she be?

00:06:06.470 --> 00:06:08.556
You don't want to get caught

00:06:11.934 --> 00:06:13.060
What is all this?

00:06:16.439 --> 00:06:17.982
I guess she's not here.

00:06:19.775 --> 00:06:21.527
There's just a whole lot of wine.

00:06:39.420 --> 00:06:40.421
Damn it.

00:06:41.923 --> 00:06:44.050
Don't just stand there. Look for her.

00:06:44.133 --> 00:06:45.885
-Sorry, sir.
-You punk.

00:06:48.012 --> 00:06:52.016
Man, where the hell is that little rat?

00:06:55.728 --> 00:06:57.355
I don't think she's over here, sir.

00:06:57.438 --> 00:06:59.523
-Did you check thoroughly?
-Yes, I did.

00:07:00.316 --> 00:07:01.275
Damn it.

00:07:05.238 --> 00:07:06.656
Where could she be hiding?

00:07:08.157 --> 00:07:10.326
-Check outside again.
-Yes, sir.

00:07:26.175 --> 00:07:29.804
Back then, everyone was talking
about the rich girl who was kidnapped.

00:07:29.887 --> 00:07:32.890
I remember moms gathering their kids
before the sun set.

00:07:33.683 --> 00:07:35.393
So you weren't abducted?

00:07:36.978 --> 00:07:39.689
The truth is, I hid in the basement

00:07:40.523 --> 00:07:41.440
for three whole days.

00:08:25.818 --> 00:08:28.279
You blew the plan
because you couldn't catch one damn kid.

00:08:29.655 --> 00:08:32.450
Who knew that kid could run that fast?

00:08:33.451 --> 00:08:34.452
But

00:08:34.535 --> 00:08:36.787
you still don't know where she is, right?

00:08:42.501 --> 00:08:45.421
What if she got out
and got hit by a car or something?

00:08:47.715 --> 00:08:50.134
I checked every emergency room
in the area.

00:08:50.718 --> 00:08:51.552
She wasn't there.

00:08:55.806 --> 00:08:57.433
Continue demanding a ransom for now.

00:08:58.225 --> 00:09:00.186
If she never returns,

00:09:01.604 --> 00:09:02.938
this will be the perfect crime.

00:09:09.403 --> 00:09:10.655
Damn it.

00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:12.114
A ransom?

00:09:13.532 --> 00:09:16.410
Are you suggesting

00:09:16.494 --> 00:09:19.497
that we pay off the abductors
to get the kid back?

00:09:20.790 --> 00:09:23.209
Do you know how much I pay in taxes?

00:09:23.292 --> 00:09:24.377
It's been three days.

00:09:24.460 --> 00:09:26.587
How can the police not find
one measly kid?

00:09:26.671 --> 00:09:28.422
We're not suggesting you pay them off.

00:09:28.964 --> 00:09:30.883
-We can use it to lure them out--
-Look here.

00:09:30.966 --> 00:09:32.635
If we pay the ransom now,

00:09:33.219 --> 00:09:36.889
she'll only become a walking target
for more abductors.

00:09:36.972 --> 00:09:38.140
Sir.

00:09:38.224 --> 00:09:40.643
If we provoke the captors,

00:09:41.310 --> 00:09:43.020
it could put Ms. Kang in danger.

00:09:43.104 --> 00:09:44.397
No.

00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:45.398
Absolutely not.

00:09:45.481 --> 00:09:48.067
We must bring back our Eun-joo,
even if it costs all our fortune.

00:09:48.150 --> 00:09:49.318
This all happened

00:09:50.069 --> 00:09:54.532
because of you, Choi In-ja,
and that silly vanity of yours!

00:09:54.615 --> 00:09:55.574
What?

00:09:55.658 --> 00:09:58.035
You paraded that kid around everywhere

00:09:58.119 --> 00:10:01.664
and plastered her face
all over the magazines and TV shows!

00:10:01.747 --> 00:10:03.124
She wasn't kidnapped out there!

00:10:03.207 --> 00:10:04.875
The burglars broke into our home!

00:10:04.959 --> 00:10:06.585
You threw a party every damn day,

00:10:06.669 --> 00:10:09.588
inviting reporters, directors,
and even studio heads.

00:10:09.672 --> 00:10:13.634
You're the one who dragged
all those strangers into this house.

00:10:13.718 --> 00:10:14.635
So?

00:10:14.719 --> 00:10:16.429
Are you just giving up on our daughter?

00:10:16.512 --> 00:10:18.556
We need to get Eun-joo back!

00:10:18.639 --> 00:10:20.725
We don't even know if she's safe,

00:10:20.808 --> 00:10:23.310
so why would we negotiate
with those scoundrels?

00:10:24.061 --> 00:10:24.979
I'd rather put

00:10:25.479 --> 00:10:28.357
a bounty on the criminals' heads instead.

00:10:29.358 --> 00:10:31.277
-Honey.
-I refuse

00:10:31.360 --> 00:10:34.655
to spend even a single cent on ransom!

00:10:36.866 --> 00:10:38.659
My poor Eun-joo!

00:10:38.743 --> 00:10:39.910
My Eun-joo…

00:10:41.245 --> 00:10:42.329
Detective…

00:10:43.789 --> 00:10:46.000
Honey, what about our Eun-joo?

00:10:49.670 --> 00:10:50.588
Where were you?

00:10:51.297 --> 00:10:52.506
In the basement.

00:10:54.383 --> 00:10:55.301
Wait…

00:10:57.052 --> 00:10:58.679
Eun-joo!

00:10:58.763 --> 00:10:59.597
Ms. Kang!

00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:01.599
-Eun-joo!
-Ms. Kang!

00:11:01.682 --> 00:11:02.600
Come here.

00:11:02.683 --> 00:11:04.560
Eun-joo!

00:11:05.728 --> 00:11:07.188
Where in the world were you?

00:11:07.271 --> 00:11:08.481
Are you hurt anywhere?

00:11:08.564 --> 00:11:10.775
Honey, our Eun-joo is back.

00:11:14.695 --> 00:11:15.613
Eun-joo…

00:11:22.995 --> 00:11:24.121
You must've been so scared.

00:11:24.205 --> 00:11:25.831
You must've been scared.

00:11:32.171 --> 00:11:34.048
It's incredible
that you made it back alive.

00:11:34.131 --> 00:11:35.591
After that incident,

00:11:36.342 --> 00:11:38.552
my mom filed for divorce,

00:11:39.053 --> 00:11:41.597
and I left for the US with her.

00:11:42.181 --> 00:11:45.351
I stopped using the name
Kang Eun-joo after that.

00:11:46.769 --> 00:11:48.145
That is, until I met you all.

00:11:48.854 --> 00:11:50.773
And you're saying the abductor from then

00:11:51.524 --> 00:11:53.734
was the same man
who tried to drag me away today?

00:11:57.571 --> 00:11:58.697
Yes, I know those eyes.

00:11:59.448 --> 00:12:00.366
It was him.

00:12:02.076 --> 00:12:04.578
I still have nightmares
about it sometimes.

00:12:05.246 --> 00:12:08.040
Ms. Song was already working
for Hanmin back then, right?

00:12:08.707 --> 00:12:09.750
By the chairman's side?

00:12:11.544 --> 00:12:15.172
Song Ju-ran wasn't just occasionally
hiring a thug to intimidate people.

00:12:16.507 --> 00:12:18.008
They've been long-time partners.

00:12:28.352 --> 00:12:29.645
Are you hurt anywhere?

00:12:30.312 --> 00:12:31.981
I'm more worried about Nora.

00:12:32.064 --> 00:12:33.691
I know it must be upsetting for her,

00:12:33.774 --> 00:12:36.986
but that kidnapping incident is
also quite a touchy subject for my family.

00:12:37.069 --> 00:12:39.071
Given the history of incidents,

00:12:39.154 --> 00:12:42.116
we need to find out Song Ju-ran's ties
to that kidnapper first.

00:12:43.158 --> 00:12:44.159
But how do we find him?

00:12:44.743 --> 00:12:45.578
We don't even know his face.

00:12:46.537 --> 00:12:48.038
You already do.

00:12:49.373 --> 00:12:50.374
Horang Auto Repair Shop.

00:12:51.667 --> 00:12:52.960
That scary guy from the repair shop?

00:12:55.045 --> 00:12:55.879
Okay.

00:12:55.963 --> 00:12:57.590
I'll help with that since I know his face.

00:12:58.966 --> 00:13:00.801
I'm sure I'll find something
if I tail Ms. Song.

00:13:03.137 --> 00:13:05.639
It's time you went public
as the head of Yeouido Pirates, Keum-bo.

00:13:06.682 --> 00:13:08.475
Once we become Hanmin's public enemy,

00:13:08.559 --> 00:13:11.895
the attention alone will be enough
to keep Hanmin in line.

00:13:17.484 --> 00:13:18.527
I concur.

00:13:18.611 --> 00:13:21.780
Let's make Hong Keum-bo's face known
across the country.

00:13:29.288 --> 00:13:31.040
Yeouido Pirates hereby declares its intent

00:13:31.123 --> 00:13:35.085
to formally participate in the management
of Hanmin Investment &amp; Securities.

00:13:35.919 --> 00:13:39.048
In order to rein in
Chairman Kang's unilateral management,

00:13:39.131 --> 00:13:41.216
Hanmin's current governance structure
must be reformed.

00:13:41.300 --> 00:13:42.217
YEOUIDO PIRATES CEO HONG KEUM-BO'S
PRESS CONFERENCE

00:13:42.301 --> 00:13:45.596
Hanmin will collapse from the inside out
if we don't take action now.

00:13:46.180 --> 00:13:49.642
Hanmin has not issued
an official statement on the matter.

00:13:49.725 --> 00:13:51.685
PERSONAL INFORMATION FORM
HONG KEUM-BO

00:13:54.647 --> 00:13:58.484
Who was the idiot division head
in charge of Hong Keum-bo?

00:13:58.567 --> 00:14:00.527
After Albert,

00:14:02.071 --> 00:14:03.656
it was Mr. Cha Jung-il.

00:14:05.366 --> 00:14:09.036
After the restructuring, she did oversee
some menial tasks in Research.

00:14:09.119 --> 00:14:11.288
She was mouthy, often defiant,

00:14:11.372 --> 00:14:14.124
and made it obvious
that she hated delivering coffee.

00:14:14.208 --> 00:14:15.876
She was good at writing reports
and translating,

00:14:15.959 --> 00:14:17.711
it was just so annoying.

00:14:17.795 --> 00:14:20.589
I thought she just looked older,
but if she's actually 35…

00:14:20.673 --> 00:14:21.924
BIRTHDATE: DECEMBER 24, 1963

00:14:22.007 --> 00:14:23.384
She's 36?

00:14:23.467 --> 00:14:25.302
Then she was a real baby face, sir.

00:14:27.429 --> 00:14:29.807
She managed to trick everyone around her.

00:14:29.890 --> 00:14:33.185
Release all of her personal details
to the press.

00:14:34.311 --> 00:14:36.355
Focus on attacking her character.

00:14:37.856 --> 00:14:38.816
You two may leave.

00:14:45.656 --> 00:14:47.825
The slush fund probe
could've been an excuse.

00:14:48.325 --> 00:14:50.577
She may have been
after the money from the start.

00:14:51.078 --> 00:14:52.830
I suspect that as well, sir.

00:15:05.009 --> 00:15:06.135
Did you know?

00:15:06.927 --> 00:15:07.886
Know what?

00:15:07.970 --> 00:15:08.929
About Ms. Hong!

00:15:11.223 --> 00:15:12.850
Mr. Lee Yong-gi, did you know?

00:15:13.934 --> 00:15:16.061
Actually, don't say anything to anyone.

00:15:16.145 --> 00:15:18.063
It'll just get you interrogated
by the chairman.

00:15:19.773 --> 00:15:21.942
Ms. Go wasn't at her desk today, was she?

00:15:22.026 --> 00:15:24.403
I heard she faxed in her resignation
and suddenly quit.

00:15:24.945 --> 00:15:25.946
I get it now.

00:15:26.530 --> 00:15:29.074
President Shin must've recruited her.

00:15:29.158 --> 00:15:31.285
He took his assistant with him.

00:15:31.368 --> 00:15:32.828
Wait a minute.

00:15:32.911 --> 00:15:36.874
What's the connection
between Hong Keum-bo and Shin Jung-woo?

00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:40.377
Maybe Ms. Go was the common link?

00:15:41.795 --> 00:15:42.713
That must be it.

00:15:43.714 --> 00:15:44.548
That means…

00:15:46.216 --> 00:15:47.176
Right?

00:15:47.259 --> 00:15:48.969
Gosh…

00:15:49.053 --> 00:15:50.012
Right?

00:15:55.059 --> 00:15:56.018
Sir.

00:15:56.560 --> 00:15:58.937
I just faxed over
Hong Keum-bo's profile to you.

00:15:59.021 --> 00:16:00.314
Hello, sir.

00:16:00.397 --> 00:16:03.192
Please make sure
the article includes those keywords.

00:16:04.109 --> 00:16:07.321
"Hong Keum-bo, breach of duty,
and moral hazard."

00:16:12.659 --> 00:16:15.204
We will certainly commit
to the advertising spend.

00:16:15.287 --> 00:16:16.455
You have my word.

00:16:16.538 --> 00:16:18.248
You have my word, sir.

00:16:18.749 --> 00:16:21.335
What are you doing? Seriously?

00:16:21.418 --> 00:16:23.087
I told you to stop taking pictures.

00:16:23.170 --> 00:16:24.463
Damn it.

00:16:24.546 --> 00:16:26.256
Then let's proceed with the interview.

00:16:26.340 --> 00:16:28.801
-Hong Keum-bo is your daughter, correct?
-Yes.

00:16:28.884 --> 00:16:30.969
Did you know about her involvement
in Yeouido Pirates?

00:16:31.053 --> 00:16:31.887
Pirates?

00:16:31.970 --> 00:16:34.389
What do you know about
your daughter's suspicious activities?

00:16:34.473 --> 00:16:36.642
Watch what you're saying, mister.

00:16:36.725 --> 00:16:37.643
Enough!

00:16:37.726 --> 00:16:39.686
We're trying to run a business here,
so leave.

00:16:39.770 --> 00:16:40.854
-Go.
-Leave!

00:16:40.938 --> 00:16:42.898
-Get out!
-Honey, be careful.

00:16:42.981 --> 00:16:44.024
Get out of here now.

00:16:44.108 --> 00:16:46.401
Leave! Go!

00:16:46.485 --> 00:16:48.070
-Be careful.
-Get out.

00:16:48.153 --> 00:16:50.114
-Leave now!
-Go!

00:16:50.197 --> 00:16:51.532
ULLALA CHICKEN

00:16:54.743 --> 00:16:56.620
Get out of here!

00:16:59.373 --> 00:17:01.750
What in the world is going on?

00:17:03.252 --> 00:17:04.378
WHO IS THE FORMER FSS INSPECTOR
"HONG KEUM-BO"?

00:17:04.461 --> 00:17:07.673
FORMER FSS INSPECTOR DECLARES INTENT
TO TAKE PART IN SECURITIES FIRM MANAGEMENT

00:17:09.216 --> 00:17:10.259
HONG KEUM-BO, CEO

00:17:10.342 --> 00:17:11.510
ETHICAL CONCERNS
AND BREACH OF DUTY ALLEGATIONS

00:17:13.053 --> 00:17:13.971
Mr. Nam.

00:17:14.054 --> 00:17:16.682
Is that rumor about Ms. Hong true?

00:17:16.765 --> 00:17:18.058
Did she leak insider information

00:17:18.142 --> 00:17:20.519
and buy stocks with private loans
she got from Myeongdong?

00:17:20.602 --> 00:17:21.728
Shut it!

00:17:21.812 --> 00:17:22.813
How would I know?

00:17:22.896 --> 00:17:26.150
There was a reason she threw herself into
investigating Hanmin's slush fund.

00:17:26.233 --> 00:17:27.276
Exactly.

00:17:27.359 --> 00:17:28.986
All that moral integrity was an act.

00:17:29.069 --> 00:17:29.987
I knew it.

00:17:33.240 --> 00:17:34.116
-I knew something was fishy…
-Move.

00:17:43.584 --> 00:17:44.543
You knew, didn't you?

00:17:45.419 --> 00:17:46.753
What did I know?

00:17:48.046 --> 00:17:51.633
Why is everyone, from top to bottom,
ripping me a new one?

00:17:52.217 --> 00:17:53.552
Do I look like her spokesperson?

00:17:53.635 --> 00:17:56.972
Is she really planning to take a shot
at Chairman Kang Pil-beom?

00:17:57.556 --> 00:17:59.600
She'll just toss away
her career and future?

00:18:05.105 --> 00:18:07.399
These articles are
just the tip of the iceberg.

00:18:07.482 --> 00:18:11.278
Rumors about her are spreading
through Yeouido, Myeongdong, and Euljiro.

00:18:11.361 --> 00:18:15.324
Did you, by any chance,
plant her inside Hanmin on purpose?

00:18:17.618 --> 00:18:18.827
Are you in on it?

00:18:19.995 --> 00:18:22.372
Do you take me for a thief, punk?

00:18:23.999 --> 00:18:24.958
Nam Dong-gi.

00:18:25.042 --> 00:18:27.586
You keep your eyes shut
and your ears covered.

00:18:27.669 --> 00:18:28.670
Got that?

00:18:28.754 --> 00:18:30.047
Damn it.

00:18:32.216 --> 00:18:33.508
What if we end up in the crossfire?

00:18:33.592 --> 00:18:35.469
Shut your mouth too! Shut it!

00:18:36.053 --> 00:18:38.639
-Get out!
-There's definitely something going on.

00:18:39.848 --> 00:18:40.933
I'm going to uncover it all.

00:18:45.479 --> 00:18:47.689
DIRECTOR YUN JAE-BEOM

00:18:50.734 --> 00:18:52.653
It's less a fight for management control

00:18:52.736 --> 00:18:53.779
and more a war of public opinion.

00:18:54.363 --> 00:18:57.532
The chairman is intent on
burying Hong Keum-bo.

00:18:58.116 --> 00:19:00.160
All those puzzle pieces
that weirdly didn't fit

00:19:00.244 --> 00:19:02.537
are finally starting to fall into place.

00:19:04.331 --> 00:19:05.624
Ms. Hong Keum-bo.

00:19:05.707 --> 00:19:07.125
So that's how

00:19:07.709 --> 00:19:11.421
she immediately knew something was up
in the Trading Division back then.

00:19:12.547 --> 00:19:13.799
How is it at the office?

00:19:13.882 --> 00:19:16.134
From the minions to the division heads,

00:19:16.218 --> 00:19:18.720
the company morale is at an all-time low.

00:19:18.804 --> 00:19:21.265
And distrust in the management
is through the roof.

00:19:21.348 --> 00:19:23.976
It's because the chairman and Ms. Song

00:19:24.059 --> 00:19:27.396
make all the decisions themselves
in their secret meetings.

00:19:27.896 --> 00:19:30.023
For the company's sake,

00:19:30.107 --> 00:19:33.318
he should sit down with Yeouido Pirates
and take them on face-to-face.

00:19:33.402 --> 00:19:35.237
My thoughts exactly.

00:19:35.320 --> 00:19:38.782
But where did Hong Keum-bo get
all that money to buy Hanmin stocks?

00:19:38.865 --> 00:19:40.492
That's the mystery.

00:19:41.076 --> 00:19:44.246
Rumors say that it's
Shin Jung-woo's personal funds,

00:19:44.329 --> 00:19:46.665
but we're talking about
hundreds of billions of won here.

00:19:57.634 --> 00:19:58.468
KANG PIL-BEOM'S FAMILY TREE

00:19:58.552 --> 00:20:00.929
According to Mr. Cha,
Hanmin has no countermeasures prepared.

00:20:01.013 --> 00:20:02.264
There's no task force either.

00:20:02.347 --> 00:20:04.641
They're solely focused on
attacking Hong Keum-bo.

00:20:05.225 --> 00:20:08.353
I think they ran the numbers
and decided she wasn't a threat,

00:20:08.437 --> 00:20:10.564
since the chairman
still holds an overwhelming stake.

00:20:11.815 --> 00:20:13.233
Nora once mentioned

00:20:13.317 --> 00:20:15.944
that if she survived
the three-month probationary period,

00:20:16.028 --> 00:20:18.989
Chairman Kang promised to reward her
with Kang Myeong-hwi's 9%.

00:20:19.072 --> 00:20:20.657
Yeah, that's right.

00:20:21.241 --> 00:20:23.618
He made that promise
after the funeral mass.

00:20:24.119 --> 00:20:26.538
Since Nora has survived
those three months,

00:20:26.621 --> 00:20:29.416
if she secures the promised 9% stake…

00:20:29.499 --> 00:20:31.043
KANG MYEONG-HWI, SON

00:20:32.461 --> 00:20:33.503
KANG PIL-BEOM

00:20:38.342 --> 00:20:39.676
KANG NORA, DAUGHTER

00:20:39.760 --> 00:20:43.680
If we add 14% to our preexisting 19,
we end up with 33%.

00:20:43.764 --> 00:20:45.766
This should be enough
to go up against Chairman Kang.

00:20:46.391 --> 00:20:49.102
Don't forget she came back
empty-handed from Switzerland.

00:20:49.186 --> 00:20:50.896
How are you so sure she'd be with us

00:20:50.979 --> 00:20:52.856
when she's about to be named
the successor?

00:20:52.939 --> 00:20:54.941
If we can't persuade her to join us,

00:20:55.025 --> 00:20:56.818
we'll need to create a rift between them.

00:20:57.778 --> 00:21:01.323
Tomorrow, we'll launch
a public tender offer for Hanmin.

00:21:02.574 --> 00:21:03.700
A public tender offer?

00:21:03.784 --> 00:21:07.162
We offer a desirable price and scoop up
shares from small shareholders.

00:21:07.245 --> 00:21:08.997
From now on, we must do whatever it takes

00:21:09.081 --> 00:21:11.041
to acquire every share we can.

00:21:13.043 --> 00:21:14.044
Okay.

00:21:23.053 --> 00:21:24.179
YEOUIDO PIRATES PLANS A SWEEP?
"WE'LL BUY THEM ALL AT HIGHER PRICES"

00:21:24.262 --> 00:21:25.222
AN ALL-OUT WAR WITH TENDER OFFER

00:21:25.305 --> 00:21:27.557
HANMIN VS YEOUIDO PIRATES
SURGE IN STOCK PRICE FUELS MARKET CHAOS

00:21:27.641 --> 00:21:29.601
HANMIN VS YEOUIDO PIRATES
BATTLE IT OUT FOR MANAGEMENT CONTROL

00:21:29.684 --> 00:21:32.813
How in the world does
Hong Keum-bo think she can pull this off?

00:21:32.896 --> 00:21:35.107
-Two rolls each. That'll be 4,000 won.
-Okay.

00:21:35.190 --> 00:21:37.776
A purchase of two rolls
comes with complementary probiotics.

00:21:37.859 --> 00:21:39.194
-Thank you.
-Sure.

00:21:39.277 --> 00:21:41.238
Thank you so much.

00:21:43.949 --> 00:21:45.033
This is a piece of cake.

00:21:50.288 --> 00:21:51.623
It's time for an honest conversation.

00:21:53.375 --> 00:21:55.127
HANMIN VS YEOUIDO PIRATES
BATTLE IT OUT FOR MANAGEMENT CONTROL

00:21:55.210 --> 00:21:56.586
Ms. Hong is involved, right?

00:22:00.340 --> 00:22:01.550
I've always

00:22:01.633 --> 00:22:03.593
wanted to befriend her.

00:22:05.387 --> 00:22:06.638
And?

00:22:08.348 --> 00:22:09.891
So I placed my shares with her.

00:22:13.270 --> 00:22:15.272
Then do you know
the source of her funds as well?

00:22:19.901 --> 00:22:20.735
Big Al.

00:22:24.906 --> 00:22:25.866
Big Al?

00:22:29.995 --> 00:22:30.912
What's gotten into you?

00:22:34.916 --> 00:22:35.834
I can't tell you everything.

00:22:35.917 --> 00:22:36.918
Okay.

00:22:38.879 --> 00:22:39.921
Our Captain Hong

00:22:41.214 --> 00:22:42.465
has a magical ledger.

00:22:42.549 --> 00:22:43.383
Yehppee!

00:22:44.009 --> 00:22:45.844
That's our seed money.

00:22:45.927 --> 00:22:47.512
Yong-gi and I have joined her.

00:22:48.096 --> 00:22:49.097
A ledger?

00:22:49.181 --> 00:22:50.223
Don't tell me…

00:22:50.307 --> 00:22:53.143
You have a copy
of the slush fund ledger, don't you?

00:22:53.226 --> 00:22:54.477
Could you maybe think of this

00:22:55.812 --> 00:22:58.648
not as a gamble
but as a final investment in me?

00:22:59.232 --> 00:23:01.151
You mean Chairman Kang's
slush fund ledger?

00:23:01.902 --> 00:23:02.736
You know about it too?

00:23:09.326 --> 00:23:10.160
Damn it!

00:23:10.243 --> 00:23:12.162
I can't believe Ms. Hong.

00:23:14.831 --> 00:23:16.041
Don't do it.

00:23:16.124 --> 00:23:17.918
-You'd better pick up, Ms. Hong.
-Come on.

00:23:19.669 --> 00:23:22.255
She'd obviously screen her calls
in a situation this critical.

00:23:22.839 --> 00:23:24.049
Damn it.

00:23:26.051 --> 00:23:28.303
Mr. Bang, that was quite an overreaction.

00:23:30.805 --> 00:23:31.848
Could it be…

00:23:33.850 --> 00:23:34.851
What?

00:23:36.811 --> 00:23:38.438
Are you upset about being left out?

00:23:38.521 --> 00:23:39.522
No.

00:23:40.649 --> 00:23:41.524
Damn it.

00:23:41.608 --> 00:23:42.859
You totally are.

00:23:42.943 --> 00:23:45.612
-Why would I be upset?
-You totally are…

00:23:45.695 --> 00:23:47.489
Why haven't you left yet?

00:23:47.572 --> 00:23:49.032
You're totally feeling left out.

00:23:49.115 --> 00:23:50.325
Why you… Go!

00:23:50.408 --> 00:23:52.285
He's 40 and upset about being left out!

00:23:52.369 --> 00:23:53.662
He's totally upset!

00:23:54.663 --> 00:23:55.497
Don't ever come back!

00:23:59.793 --> 00:24:00.627
Damn it.

00:24:02.754 --> 00:24:03.755
Get your gimbap here!

00:24:06.383 --> 00:24:07.550
They're 1,000 won each!

00:24:22.399 --> 00:24:23.400
The chairman

00:24:24.818 --> 00:24:27.487
gave the order
to withdraw the VIP's slush fund.

00:24:27.570 --> 00:24:29.489
Are we sure we can touch that?

00:24:29.572 --> 00:24:30.657
Given who we're up against--

00:24:30.740 --> 00:24:33.868
We still have a year
until the interest payments are paid out.

00:24:33.952 --> 00:24:36.246
We can dip into it at our discretion

00:24:36.955 --> 00:24:38.999
and just top it back up
by the end of the year.

00:24:54.681 --> 00:24:55.849
Oh, boy.

00:24:59.644 --> 00:25:01.479
-There's nothing?
-They're all empty.

00:25:03.106 --> 00:25:05.525
They've all been withdrawn
with zero balances.

00:25:07.277 --> 00:25:10.030
Those seals never left that safe.

00:25:10.113 --> 00:25:12.490
The bankbooks, copies of IDs,
and the authorization letters

00:25:12.574 --> 00:25:14.159
are all with me!

00:25:17.662 --> 00:25:18.997
Is it Hong Keum-bo's doing again?

00:25:19.998 --> 00:25:22.375
You must have checked who withdrew it!

00:25:23.460 --> 00:25:28.131
All the funds were transferred
to Yeouido Pirates' corporate account.

00:25:31.801 --> 00:25:33.595
Hey, I think it's time

00:25:33.678 --> 00:25:35.096
we just secure what's ours now.

00:25:36.598 --> 00:25:37.599
Come on.

00:25:37.682 --> 00:25:40.935
-It's still not too late.
-Don't be a moron.

00:25:41.853 --> 00:25:42.687
I did not

00:25:42.771 --> 00:25:44.773
devote myself to Hanmin

00:25:45.440 --> 00:25:49.235
for 30 damn years for some chump change!

00:25:55.116 --> 00:25:56.284
Now, the chairman

00:25:57.202 --> 00:25:59.871
couldn't get rid of me,
even if he wanted to.

00:26:00.580 --> 00:26:01.498
He has no one left.

00:26:27.357 --> 00:26:28.400
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

00:26:28.483 --> 00:26:29.692
What did you say?

00:26:30.819 --> 00:26:32.112
My apologies, sir.

00:26:32.195 --> 00:26:34.364
It seems Hong Keum-bo's team
stole those funds,

00:26:34.447 --> 00:26:37.075
knowing we couldn't report it publicly.

00:26:37.158 --> 00:26:40.620
How could they have possibly
stolen the VIP's slush fund?

00:26:40.703 --> 00:26:44.207
You and I are the only ones
who know about its existence!

00:26:44.290 --> 00:26:45.792
I fear Executive Director Oh--

00:26:45.875 --> 00:26:47.001
Hey!

00:26:47.502 --> 00:26:49.754
He only ever delivered
the interest payments.

00:26:49.838 --> 00:26:50.797
It was managed

00:26:51.297 --> 00:26:53.925
by you, Song Ju-ran!

00:26:55.468 --> 00:27:00.390
You accused Oh Deok-gyu
of stealing the OW slush fund.

00:27:01.683 --> 00:27:04.519
But he said he was innocent!

00:27:05.186 --> 00:27:06.396
The way I see it,

00:27:06.479 --> 00:27:10.442
you framed Oh Deok-gyu back then
to hide the fact that it was stolen,

00:27:10.525 --> 00:27:14.320
and now you've
stupidly let it spiral into this!

00:27:14.404 --> 00:27:15.238
That's not true.

00:27:15.321 --> 00:27:16.823
Please believe me, sir.

00:27:17.657 --> 00:27:19.784
Last summer, during the slush fund probe,

00:27:19.868 --> 00:27:24.289
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi
made contact with Hong Keum-bo, didn't he?

00:27:24.372 --> 00:27:27.375
I fear he may have
handed something over to her back then.

00:27:30.128 --> 00:27:31.671
Goddamn it!

00:27:32.338 --> 00:27:35.216
Goddamn it all!

00:27:35.300 --> 00:27:38.386
We should first request
additional financing from DK Ventures

00:27:39.512 --> 00:27:41.222
to roll over the maturing bonds--

00:27:41.306 --> 00:27:42.515
Shut it!

00:27:43.183 --> 00:27:45.810
Are you seriously suggesting that
as an option right now?

00:27:46.853 --> 00:27:47.937
Are you telling me

00:27:48.021 --> 00:27:52.609
I should go beg for another handout
from that damn weasel?

00:27:58.198 --> 00:27:59.449
Unbelievable.

00:28:04.370 --> 00:28:07.248
We were only supposed to use Hanmin
as a basecamp.

00:28:07.790 --> 00:28:09.876
You once bought Hanmin bonds with me,

00:28:09.959 --> 00:28:12.795
but now you're snapping up stocks
at Yeouido Pirates?

00:28:13.379 --> 00:28:14.506
You're doing the complete opposite.

00:28:15.757 --> 00:28:16.883
With what money?

00:28:16.966 --> 00:28:18.259
We have enough funds.

00:28:18.343 --> 00:28:20.220
Your bonds will become worthless

00:28:20.303 --> 00:28:23.181
if Yeouido Pirates
becomes the controlling shareholder.

00:28:23.723 --> 00:28:25.183
So choose wisely,

00:28:25.683 --> 00:28:28.645
and remember that
Yeouido Pirates and I are key variables.

00:28:30.355 --> 00:28:34.025
Chairman Kang will reach out to you
to cover the bond maturity next week.

00:28:34.692 --> 00:28:35.818
If I were you,

00:28:35.902 --> 00:28:37.111
I would turn him down.

00:28:38.738 --> 00:28:41.366
But Chairman Kang will retaliate.

00:28:41.449 --> 00:28:44.494
So you'll pour money down the drain
because you're afraid?

00:28:45.370 --> 00:28:48.248
I'm giving you a chance to make your exit.

00:28:55.338 --> 00:28:56.256
Please eat.

00:29:00.635 --> 00:29:01.636
Eat.

00:29:06.724 --> 00:29:08.309
Chairman, I…

00:29:15.108 --> 00:29:16.025
Sir.

00:29:16.109 --> 00:29:19.237
The chairman just barely managed
to take his first bite.

00:29:19.320 --> 00:29:20.196
What could be so…

00:29:22.699 --> 00:29:26.411
DK Ventures faxed a notice of intent
to withdraw from the investment agreement.

00:29:26.494 --> 00:29:27.745
What did you say?

00:29:30.623 --> 00:29:32.375
INVESTMENT AGREEMENT WITHDRAWAL
AND BOND SALE NOTICE

00:29:32.458 --> 00:29:33.960
These bastards!

00:29:34.460 --> 00:29:36.421
-Get them on the phone!
-Yes, sir.

00:29:36.504 --> 00:29:37.964
I can't believe this.

00:29:47.348 --> 00:29:49.058
He's not picking up?

00:29:49.559 --> 00:29:50.560
Why this little…

00:29:57.734 --> 00:29:58.568
Nora.

00:29:58.651 --> 00:30:00.987
Is the company on shaky ground right now?

00:30:01.070 --> 00:30:01.905
How would I know?

00:30:03.865 --> 00:30:06.075
Get back in there
and at least pretend to be worried.

00:30:06.159 --> 00:30:07.327
Go on. Hurry.

00:30:07.410 --> 00:30:08.828
How could I when I know nothing?

00:30:08.912 --> 00:30:10.830
You just dragged me out.

00:30:12.373 --> 00:30:13.666
Seriously?

00:30:16.920 --> 00:30:19.881
DK Ventures has notified Hanmin
of the withdrawal of its investment,

00:30:19.964 --> 00:30:21.466
but our situation isn't ideal either.

00:30:22.717 --> 00:30:24.385
Stock prices jumped
because of the tender offers,

00:30:24.469 --> 00:30:26.930
and we're burning through our funds
to buy shares.

00:30:46.199 --> 00:30:47.367
They seemed really close.

00:30:47.951 --> 00:30:50.411
It appeared to be more than
a mere work-for-hire arrangement.

00:30:51.079 --> 00:30:52.497
You'll use this against her, right?

00:30:52.580 --> 00:30:54.332
We can't afford to hold back right now.

00:31:10.682 --> 00:31:14.102
The one-percent stake in Hanmin I received
from the divorce settlement?

00:31:15.061 --> 00:31:17.188
You want me to take your side with that?

00:31:21.317 --> 00:31:22.235
Why would I do that?

00:31:23.319 --> 00:31:24.862
We might not be husband and wife anymore,

00:31:24.946 --> 00:31:28.533
but he and I are still connected
through our Nora.

00:31:28.616 --> 00:31:31.035
So why would I betray the chairman?

00:31:38.918 --> 00:31:39.919
Nora.

00:31:40.920 --> 00:31:44.257
Do you recognize the man
sitting next to Ms. Song?

00:31:47.719 --> 00:31:48.970
What in the world is this?

00:31:49.053 --> 00:31:50.304
Ms. Song has a man she's seeing?

00:31:50.388 --> 00:31:53.266
The man who tried to abduct Kang Eun-joo
when she was ten…

00:31:54.976 --> 00:31:55.893
That's him, isn't it?

00:31:58.396 --> 00:32:00.148
My goodness. Hold on.

00:32:00.940 --> 00:32:02.984
Why would Ms. Song do that?

00:32:03.067 --> 00:32:04.277
How dare she go after our bloodline?

00:32:04.360 --> 00:32:07.989
Albert and I also suspect
that these two people instigated

00:32:08.072 --> 00:32:10.158
President Kang Myeong-hwi's accident.

00:32:11.242 --> 00:32:13.077
What? Myeong-hwi's accident?

00:32:13.745 --> 00:32:16.789
Does that mean
Albert's accusation was true?

00:32:18.082 --> 00:32:19.709
Even if it's just for Nora's safety,

00:32:19.792 --> 00:32:21.711
we need you to take a stand.

00:32:45.276 --> 00:32:47.945
What do you think you're doing?

00:32:48.029 --> 00:32:49.280
When Nora was ten,

00:32:49.822 --> 00:32:53.409
we had intruders break into our home
and attempt to kidnap her.

00:32:53.493 --> 00:32:55.244
Even back then,

00:32:55.328 --> 00:32:57.330
the police suspected an insider job.

00:32:57.413 --> 00:32:58.790
And today,

00:32:58.873 --> 00:33:00.208
I finally found the accomplice.

00:33:00.833 --> 00:33:01.959
Chairman,

00:33:02.043 --> 00:33:04.420
this woman has been deceiving us
this whole time!

00:33:05.421 --> 00:33:07.799
Where did you get these photos from?

00:33:07.882 --> 00:33:09.967
You'll answer my question first.

00:33:10.051 --> 00:33:11.052
It was you, wasn't it?

00:33:12.386 --> 00:33:13.304
No.

00:33:14.347 --> 00:33:15.348
This is a misunderstanding.

00:33:16.057 --> 00:33:16.891
A misunderstanding?

00:33:16.974 --> 00:33:19.852
You were also behind
Myeong-hwi's accident, weren't you?

00:33:19.936 --> 00:33:20.770
Am I wrong about this too?

00:33:21.354 --> 00:33:22.230
Come on now.

00:33:22.313 --> 00:33:23.898
It's all in the past now--

00:33:23.981 --> 00:33:26.109
Why won't you believe me?

00:33:26.901 --> 00:33:30.822
Our Nora remembers
that kidnapper's face to this day.

00:33:31.739 --> 00:33:33.741
Are you certain?

00:33:34.992 --> 00:33:35.827
Yes.

00:33:36.452 --> 00:33:38.162
Ms. Song,

00:33:38.246 --> 00:33:40.289
why don't you explain
those pictures first?

00:33:45.378 --> 00:33:46.546
An old friend from my hometown

00:33:47.130 --> 00:33:49.590
kept calling
because he was strapped for cash.

00:33:49.674 --> 00:33:53.010
So I gave him a little something
and sent him on his way.

00:33:53.094 --> 00:33:55.054
I hadn't seen him in ten years.

00:33:55.555 --> 00:33:58.432
And as for that kidnapping incident,

00:33:59.016 --> 00:34:00.685
are you sure you're not mistaken,
Ms. Kang?

00:34:01.644 --> 00:34:03.062
It was so long ago,

00:34:03.146 --> 00:34:05.022
and you were just a child.

00:34:06.691 --> 00:34:07.567
Sir.

00:34:08.484 --> 00:34:12.363
I've never had a reason
to do something like that.

00:34:17.118 --> 00:34:18.286
If anything,

00:34:18.369 --> 00:34:23.457
I care about Ms. Kang
more than you ever have, ma'am.

00:34:23.541 --> 00:34:24.876
You're being

00:34:25.751 --> 00:34:26.836
far too emotional right now.

00:34:26.919 --> 00:34:29.005
-What? Emotional?
-Mom!

00:34:29.088 --> 00:34:30.882
Of course I'm emotional about my family.

00:34:30.965 --> 00:34:32.008
She's my daughter!

00:34:32.091 --> 00:34:35.511
Listen, we have bigger fires
to put out at the company.

00:34:35.595 --> 00:34:37.305
Let's talk about this later.

00:34:38.931 --> 00:34:40.224
I should've never

00:34:40.308 --> 00:34:42.476
come back to this damn house.

00:34:56.032 --> 00:34:57.867
He's just a friend
who runs errands for me.

00:34:58.701 --> 00:34:59.911
But I can swear to you

00:34:59.994 --> 00:35:02.914
I had no part in Ms. Kang's kidnapping.

00:35:04.123 --> 00:35:07.460
Let's focus on company matters for now.

00:35:10.296 --> 00:35:11.130
Yes, sir.

00:35:37.990 --> 00:35:39.116
Auntie,

00:35:39.617 --> 00:35:43.329
did you also move out with your mom then?

00:35:44.872 --> 00:35:47.041
I couldn't let her leave by herself.

00:35:47.959 --> 00:35:51.379
If I'm being honest,
I knew my father would do that.

00:36:00.054 --> 00:36:02.056
This is my favorite hairpin.

00:36:03.474 --> 00:36:06.394
This is a secret,
but wearing it gives you strength.

00:36:12.692 --> 00:36:13.859
Thanks.

00:36:24.662 --> 00:36:26.831
She's a celebrity.
We should get an autograph.

00:36:27.999 --> 00:36:28.958
She's our daughter's guest.

00:36:29.041 --> 00:36:30.584
Behave yourself, will you?

00:36:37.717 --> 00:36:39.010
We'll give you some privacy.

00:36:39.677 --> 00:36:41.220
Hello, I'm a big fan…

00:36:42.638 --> 00:36:44.181
I can't even get an autograph?

00:36:45.266 --> 00:36:46.600
Are you all right, ma'am?

00:36:48.686 --> 00:36:50.146
Of course not.

00:36:58.487 --> 00:37:02.241
I only came all this way

00:37:02.325 --> 00:37:06.078
because you came to me first
without going to the press.

00:37:07.163 --> 00:37:08.581
I figured I should at least thank you.

00:37:09.957 --> 00:37:12.585
Did you get a chance to speak to Ms. Song?

00:37:15.504 --> 00:37:16.547
She just denied it.

00:37:17.131 --> 00:37:19.425
But I know it was her doing.

00:37:20.009 --> 00:37:24.305
She was always dying to split up
the chairman and me.

00:37:25.056 --> 00:37:26.182
A misunderstanding?

00:37:26.265 --> 00:37:27.850
Misunderstanding, my ass.

00:37:28.476 --> 00:37:29.393
Damn wench.

00:37:40.196 --> 00:37:42.990
The one-percent stake I have in Hanmin…

00:37:44.116 --> 00:37:45.201
I'll give it to you.

00:37:46.077 --> 00:37:46.911
But

00:37:47.411 --> 00:37:48.412
keep Nora out of it.

00:37:49.789 --> 00:37:50.790
Pardon?

00:37:50.873 --> 00:37:53.042
Don't link my decision to hers.

00:37:53.125 --> 00:37:55.336
You're smart, so I assume you understand.

00:37:56.879 --> 00:37:58.756
Yes, I understand.

00:38:24.115 --> 00:38:25.991
Ms. Kang came into work today.

00:38:26.951 --> 00:38:28.077
Is that so?

00:38:28.160 --> 00:38:30.746
And I've confirmed
that an assistant who recently quit

00:38:30.830 --> 00:38:33.582
has joined Yeouido Pirates.

00:38:33.666 --> 00:38:34.708
And who might that be?

00:38:34.792 --> 00:38:37.169
It's Go Bok-hee,
Mr. Shin Jung-woo's former assistant.

00:38:38.003 --> 00:38:39.255
After some investigating,

00:38:39.338 --> 00:38:40.923
I've learned that she was accused

00:38:41.674 --> 00:38:43.092
of embezzlement at her previous jobs.

00:38:45.010 --> 00:38:46.762
So these punks were running

00:38:47.346 --> 00:38:50.599
a whole syndicate to steal the slush fund.

00:38:51.225 --> 00:38:54.854
I believe we can use their past histories
to question the origin of their funds

00:38:56.105 --> 00:38:59.442
and arrange a small commotion for them.

00:39:02.695 --> 00:39:03.529
We must face them.

00:39:05.322 --> 00:39:07.700
Mr. Lee, you still work there,
so you're out.

00:39:09.869 --> 00:39:11.287
The three of us should go.

00:39:11.370 --> 00:39:13.038
What? Why are you excluding me?

00:39:13.122 --> 00:39:15.166
Ms. Song's out to get you.

00:39:15.249 --> 00:39:16.584
Who knows what trap awaits us?

00:39:16.667 --> 00:39:19.879
I'm sure she holds
a far deeper grudge against you.

00:39:19.962 --> 00:39:22.715
She even sent Go Bok-cheol
to my parents' restaurant.

00:39:22.798 --> 00:39:25.092
She also threatened you
with your embezzlement history.

00:39:26.260 --> 00:39:27.386
Exactly.

00:39:27.470 --> 00:39:30.514
I'm sick of running scared
and packing up when it's time.

00:39:33.017 --> 00:39:35.769
I'm done running away now.

00:40:04.590 --> 00:40:07.134
I'll hide the ashtray
as soon as we enter his office.

00:40:07.676 --> 00:40:08.969
My grandpa could throw it at us.

00:40:38.791 --> 00:40:40.834
You've had numerous meetings
with Chairman Kang.

00:40:40.918 --> 00:40:42.044
Has this ever happened?

00:40:42.127 --> 00:40:43.087
No.

00:40:43.170 --> 00:40:44.964
I don't see Ms. Song either.

00:40:53.806 --> 00:40:56.392
Go Bok-hee, you're under arrest
for embezzlement and theft.

00:40:56.475 --> 00:40:59.353
You have the right to remain silent
and the right to an attorney.

00:40:59.436 --> 00:41:00.521
What?

00:41:00.604 --> 00:41:02.481
We can talk more at the station.

00:41:02.565 --> 00:41:03.732
-Take her.
-Yes, sir.

00:41:03.816 --> 00:41:04.650
Wait.

00:41:05.234 --> 00:41:06.485
-My goodness.
-Let's go.

00:41:10.364 --> 00:41:11.282
Hold on.

00:41:12.283 --> 00:41:15.119
This isn't Ms. Go's workplace or her home.

00:41:15.202 --> 00:41:17.997
Who told you that she'd be here today?

00:41:19.081 --> 00:41:21.417
Please step aside.
We can't reveal our sources.

00:41:24.044 --> 00:41:25.504
-Let's go.
-Wait…

00:41:25.588 --> 00:41:27.381
Hold on a second. Wait!

00:41:28.507 --> 00:41:29.383
Hold on!

00:41:54.575 --> 00:41:56.619
I gave you several chances.

00:41:57.244 --> 00:41:58.787
Unfortunately, you're the weakest link.

00:42:01.373 --> 00:42:02.625
That's why you're the first to go.

00:42:08.172 --> 00:42:11.425
Then I guess you're next, Ms. Song?

00:42:12.551 --> 00:42:14.261
You're not much better off than me.

00:42:19.850 --> 00:42:22.436
How do you manage to maintain
such a calm smile on your face

00:42:22.519 --> 00:42:25.314
when the higher-ups
spew nonsense and dig into you?

00:42:29.526 --> 00:42:30.402
It's so I don't lose.

00:42:34.198 --> 00:42:36.909
You lose if you show tears
or falter in that moment.

00:42:38.327 --> 00:42:41.121
I know how I really feel
behind that smile.

00:42:48.837 --> 00:42:50.339
I'll go with her and get her a lawyer.

00:43:02.184 --> 00:43:03.227
Let's reschedule the meeting.

00:43:04.520 --> 00:43:05.938
Get back safely.

00:43:22.996 --> 00:43:25.791
ULLALA CHICKEN

00:43:25.874 --> 00:43:30.003
I was so shocked to see Ms. Go
walk out of the lobby in handcuffs.

00:43:31.505 --> 00:43:32.715
She'll be out in no time.

00:43:32.798 --> 00:43:34.633
Breaking into Ms. Song's safe?

00:43:34.717 --> 00:43:36.552
What could Ms. Song tell the police?

00:43:37.261 --> 00:43:40.556
The police weren't charging her
with anything related to Hanmin.

00:43:41.056 --> 00:43:44.309
Ms. Go was suspected of embezzlement
and theft by her former employers

00:43:44.393 --> 00:43:46.520
before she even joined Hanmin.

00:43:46.603 --> 00:43:47.813
Embezzlement?

00:43:47.896 --> 00:43:49.148
She can tell them it's not true.

00:43:49.231 --> 00:43:51.108
How can she when it's the truth?

00:43:51.191 --> 00:43:53.193
You of all people can't say that.

00:43:53.277 --> 00:43:55.154
Don't you remember what Queen Bee told us?

00:43:55.237 --> 00:43:57.239
She said she was never once caught.

00:43:57.322 --> 00:43:59.074
And she still wouldn't have been caught

00:43:59.158 --> 00:44:02.119
if she hadn't gotten involved with you
or this Yeouido Pirates business.

00:44:02.202 --> 00:44:03.537
So are you saying it's my fault?

00:44:03.620 --> 00:44:06.248
You say whatever you want
and order everyone around.

00:44:06.331 --> 00:44:07.499
Why can't I?

00:44:08.667 --> 00:44:09.835
Auntie, what's wrong with you?

00:44:09.918 --> 00:44:11.336
I'm not like Albert.

00:44:11.420 --> 00:44:13.422
I don't want to be arrested
like Queen Bee.

00:44:15.466 --> 00:44:18.218
Don't think I'll do as you say
just because everyone else does.

00:44:23.140 --> 00:44:23.974
Wait.

00:44:53.337 --> 00:44:54.171
Ju-ran.

00:44:55.255 --> 00:44:56.507
It appears the soft-hearted Nora

00:44:57.216 --> 00:44:59.635
has turned on Yeouido Pirates.

00:45:02.846 --> 00:45:05.474
PAST EMBEZZLEMENT ALLEGATIONS SURFACE
AGAINST KEY MEMBER OF YEOUIDO PIRATES

00:45:05.557 --> 00:45:08.268
FUNDING SOURCES OF YEOUIDO PIRATES'
VAST CAPITAL COME UNDER SCRUTINY

00:45:09.061 --> 00:45:10.103
THE BEAUTIFUL EMBEZZLER MS. GO'S SECRETS

00:45:10.187 --> 00:45:11.021
Ms. Go.

00:45:12.272 --> 00:45:14.650
They featured a nice picture of you.

00:45:16.360 --> 00:45:18.946
Anyway, you should be more worried
about Kang Nora than me.

00:45:19.029 --> 00:45:21.240
We're supposed to be
meeting her again today.

00:45:21.323 --> 00:45:23.242
Try to talk her into it, President Shin.

00:45:23.951 --> 00:45:24.993
And you stay out of it.

00:45:25.077 --> 00:45:26.912
You should worry about yourself.

00:45:28.080 --> 00:45:30.582
I don't want to lose anymore either.

00:45:32.376 --> 00:45:34.169
Speaking of, let me say one thing.

00:45:36.380 --> 00:45:37.214
I want…

00:45:42.094 --> 00:45:43.762
the most expensive lawyer in the country.

00:45:44.513 --> 00:45:46.181
You have some money left over.

00:45:46.265 --> 00:45:47.349
Help me avoid detention,

00:45:47.432 --> 00:45:49.518
so even if I'm locked up later,
it'll be a short stint.

00:45:49.601 --> 00:45:50.602
Okay?

00:45:51.228 --> 00:45:52.229
Okay.

00:46:05.158 --> 00:46:07.452
You ignored that call

00:46:07.536 --> 00:46:09.913
almost as if you knew who was calling.

00:46:10.497 --> 00:46:12.291
Ms. Hong Keum-bo asked to meet today,

00:46:12.374 --> 00:46:13.458
but I didn't go.

00:46:14.376 --> 00:46:15.794
I see.

00:46:15.877 --> 00:46:20.048
I had you work in the company

00:46:20.132 --> 00:46:22.843
and live in the dorms

00:46:22.926 --> 00:46:24.720
because I wanted you

00:46:24.803 --> 00:46:28.307
to experience an ordinary, modest life.

00:46:29.850 --> 00:46:32.519
But it seems three months in the dorm

00:46:33.103 --> 00:46:36.273
brought you quite close to your roommates.

00:46:36.940 --> 00:46:38.859
I heard you visited one of them

00:46:38.942 --> 00:46:41.528
when she was in the hospital
not too long ago,

00:46:41.612 --> 00:46:45.032
and even went to the restaurant
that Hong Keum-bo's parents run.

00:46:45.949 --> 00:46:48.785
I shared a room with the one
who was hospitalized.

00:46:49.578 --> 00:46:52.080
She's a single mother of a little girl.

00:46:52.164 --> 00:46:55.542
They reminded me
of my time with Mom in the US,

00:46:55.626 --> 00:46:57.044
so I wanted to take good care of them.

00:46:57.127 --> 00:46:58.670
I see.

00:46:59.671 --> 00:47:00.881
But you know,

00:47:00.964 --> 00:47:03.759
misguided sympathy is toxic.

00:47:04.384 --> 00:47:05.719
Those friends,

00:47:05.802 --> 00:47:07.095
your mother,

00:47:07.179 --> 00:47:09.097
and even your younger self.

00:47:10.223 --> 00:47:13.977
You need to let them all go
in order to grow.

00:47:15.312 --> 00:47:18.065
You need to put yourself first now.

00:47:19.650 --> 00:47:20.484
Then,

00:47:21.568 --> 00:47:23.111
I'd like you to keep your word as well.

00:47:24.237 --> 00:47:26.073
You said if I survived
the first three months here,

00:47:26.156 --> 00:47:28.158
I would get Myeong-hwi's shares.

00:47:30.077 --> 00:47:31.995
I'm going to put myself first now.

00:47:32.704 --> 00:47:33.705
Right.

00:47:33.789 --> 00:47:34.790
Sure.

00:47:40.837 --> 00:47:42.005
I've got breaking news.

00:47:43.006 --> 00:47:45.676
President Kang Nora now owns
9% more of the company.

00:47:45.759 --> 00:47:47.511
That brings her stake to 14%.

00:47:47.594 --> 00:47:48.929
How do you know about that?

00:47:49.012 --> 00:47:50.472
A shareholding disclosure was filed.

00:47:50.555 --> 00:47:52.057
Why were you looking at that?

00:47:52.140 --> 00:47:54.309
As a member
of Hanmin Investment &amp; Securities,

00:47:54.393 --> 00:47:57.020
at this critical time
when leadership is shifting…

00:47:58.146 --> 00:47:59.439
I can't just watch from the sidelines.

00:48:01.441 --> 00:48:05.153
I hear the chairman has been busy
parading her around after the transfer.

00:48:05.237 --> 00:48:08.031
It makes sense,
since he'd pay less in transfer taxes

00:48:08.115 --> 00:48:09.950
while the stock price is dismal.

00:48:10.033 --> 00:48:11.952
Why are you worrying
about rich people's taxes?

00:48:12.035 --> 00:48:13.370
I'm not worrying about the rich,

00:48:13.453 --> 00:48:16.164
I'm worrying about the company and myself.

00:48:16.248 --> 00:48:19.626
I should at least keep an eye
on where this company is headed.

00:48:22.462 --> 00:48:25.132
Mr. Lee Yong-gi,

00:48:25.215 --> 00:48:27.759
you couldn't even
look me in the eyes before.

00:48:30.220 --> 00:48:31.555
Look at that.

00:48:31.638 --> 00:48:33.682
Now, you talk back every chance you get.

00:48:33.765 --> 00:48:35.058
You've changed.

00:48:35.142 --> 00:48:36.476
I don't believe I've changed.

00:48:36.560 --> 00:48:38.145
I believe I've grown.

00:48:39.062 --> 00:48:39.896
If you'll excuse me.

00:48:43.108 --> 00:48:44.109
Unbelievable.

00:48:45.569 --> 00:48:46.528
Why is he perfectly fine?

00:48:47.154 --> 00:48:48.613
Humans are social creatures.

00:48:48.697 --> 00:48:49.948
Everyone has left.

00:48:50.741 --> 00:48:51.825
Why isn't he lonely?

00:48:54.369 --> 00:48:55.495
Why is this still so hot?

00:48:55.579 --> 00:48:58.081
The court has approved
Yeouido Pirates' request to convene

00:48:58.165 --> 00:49:00.083
an extraordinary shareholders' meeting.

00:49:01.668 --> 00:49:03.295
Unbelievable.

00:49:03.378 --> 00:49:04.963
What is the agenda item

00:49:05.046 --> 00:49:08.133
the Pirates want to raise
at the shareholders' meeting?

00:49:12.262 --> 00:49:13.472
It's the removal

00:49:14.222 --> 00:49:15.515
of Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

00:49:26.276 --> 00:49:27.569
Fine.

00:49:27.652 --> 00:49:29.154
Let's just keep our course.

00:49:30.322 --> 00:49:32.491
I, Kang Pil-beom,
am the controlling shareholder.

00:49:33.658 --> 00:49:37.245
Those bastards can't kick me out.

00:49:40.081 --> 00:49:41.291
Damn it.

00:49:42.459 --> 00:49:44.628
The date of the shareholders' meeting
has been set.

00:49:44.711 --> 00:49:47.047
It'll be February 23, 1998,
7 a.m. at the head office.

00:49:48.340 --> 00:49:49.216
At seven o'clock?

00:49:49.966 --> 00:49:51.551
That's awfully early.

00:49:51.635 --> 00:49:53.762
It's a petty trick
to deter shareholders from attending.

00:49:53.845 --> 00:49:57.224
Let's line up some shareholder disruptors
and control the mood at the meeting.

00:49:57.307 --> 00:49:58.391
Disruptors?

00:49:58.475 --> 00:50:00.727
They're paid plants
who get hired to steer the mood

00:50:00.811 --> 00:50:01.645
at shareholders' meetings.

00:50:02.229 --> 00:50:03.104
I see.

00:50:03.188 --> 00:50:04.231
So we're putting on a show?

00:50:04.314 --> 00:50:05.232
That's right.

00:50:05.315 --> 00:50:08.193
They'll try to stop us on the first floor,
so we'll split up to gain access.

00:50:08.276 --> 00:50:11.655
We'll send out press kits in bulk
and pack the meeting with reporters.

00:50:13.657 --> 00:50:15.826
Make sure to shut down any scenario

00:50:16.326 --> 00:50:18.286
that puts us
at a disadvantage in the vote.

00:50:18.370 --> 00:50:23.124
Start with strict ID checks
at the first-floor entrance,

00:50:23.208 --> 00:50:27.003
and pull in some able-bodied male staff
from the branches to stand guard.

00:50:27.712 --> 00:50:29.798
Our people should be the only ones

00:50:29.881 --> 00:50:32.384
inside the shareholders' meeting hall.

00:50:32.467 --> 00:50:34.553
-Yes, sir. Understood.
-Yes, sir. Understood.

00:50:36.179 --> 00:50:37.222
Good.

00:50:43.812 --> 00:50:44.813
Hey, Mi-sook.

00:50:44.896 --> 00:50:49.067
I heard the branch manager
and male employees talking earlier.

00:50:51.862 --> 00:50:53.905
Two staff members from Magang Branch alone

00:50:53.989 --> 00:50:55.657
have been recruited
for the shareholders' meeting.

00:50:56.157 --> 00:50:58.410
Last time, they had young male employees

00:50:58.493 --> 00:51:02.122
buy exactly one stock,
and then reimbursed them in cash.

00:51:02.831 --> 00:51:03.748
I see.

00:51:05.750 --> 00:51:08.253
Then some of the people fired
in the last restructuring

00:51:08.336 --> 00:51:10.881
must still own a Hanmin stock, right?

00:51:11.631 --> 00:51:12.716
Right.

00:51:12.799 --> 00:51:14.301
All right. Thanks.

00:51:16.219 --> 00:51:19.389
What if fired employees were mobilized
for past shareholders' meetings?

00:51:19.472 --> 00:51:22.017
They'd have a share of Hanmin stock

00:51:22.100 --> 00:51:23.977
and be eligible to attend the meeting.

00:51:28.982 --> 00:51:30.692
EMERGENCY CONTACT LIST

00:51:30.775 --> 00:51:33.486
I'm calling about
the Hanmin shareholders' meeting.

00:51:33.570 --> 00:51:35.488
-Is this Mr. Kim from Sales?
-Yes.

00:51:35.572 --> 00:51:36.990
That's correct.

00:51:37.073 --> 00:51:38.158
Do you still own a share?

00:51:38.241 --> 00:51:40.493
Thank you for joining. We'll see you then.

00:51:40.577 --> 00:51:41.703
You sold it?

00:51:41.786 --> 00:51:43.121
I understand. Thank you.

00:51:43.204 --> 00:51:45.081
TRADING DIVISION
GENERAL MANAGER, SO GYEONG-DONG

00:51:50.253 --> 00:51:53.548
GENERAL MANAGER, SO GYEONG-DONG

00:51:53.632 --> 00:51:56.134
RESIGNED

00:52:00.263 --> 00:52:02.682
EXTRAORDINARY SHAREHOLDERS' MEETING
FEBRUARY 23, 1998

00:52:04.100 --> 00:52:05.435
Come this way.

00:52:05.518 --> 00:52:06.561
Please wait.

00:52:07.812 --> 00:52:08.647
Please come through.

00:52:14.569 --> 00:52:15.695
What's that about?

00:52:16.988 --> 00:52:18.281
Do we go for the front door?

00:52:19.366 --> 00:52:20.909
-Or a side door?
-Both?

00:52:21.493 --> 00:52:24.162
I'll go for the back entrance,
so draw some attention at the front.

00:52:25.997 --> 00:52:27.540
-Let's go.
-All right.

00:52:35.882 --> 00:52:37.050
Let's go!

00:52:53.316 --> 00:52:54.985
I'm a Hanmin shareholder.

00:52:55.568 --> 00:52:56.528
I belong here!

00:52:57.112 --> 00:52:58.154
Are you kidding me?

00:52:58.655 --> 00:52:59.489
What's wrong with you?

00:53:00.907 --> 00:53:02.409
We'll need time to check the names.

00:53:02.492 --> 00:53:03.785
Please wait.

00:53:16.423 --> 00:53:20.301
EXTRAORDINARY SHAREHOLDERS' MEETING
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

00:53:34.691 --> 00:53:35.942
You all showed up early.

00:53:38.361 --> 00:53:39.279
All right.

00:53:40.697 --> 00:53:42.198
You're all here so early.

00:53:42.949 --> 00:53:44.242
Yes, hello.

00:53:45.660 --> 00:53:46.578
Hello there.

00:54:05.430 --> 00:54:06.973
They're out front.

00:54:18.985 --> 00:54:20.737
The extraordinary shareholders' meeting

00:54:20.820 --> 00:54:23.698
will commence promptly at seven o'clock.

00:54:41.508 --> 00:54:42.342
Charge!

00:54:54.896 --> 00:54:56.523
The meeting will be on the fifth floor,

00:54:56.606 --> 00:54:58.149
so I'll leave the emergency exit open.

00:55:03.988 --> 00:55:05.198
This can't be.

00:55:10.078 --> 00:55:10.995
TEMPORARILY CLOSED

00:55:12.789 --> 00:55:13.998
Hello.

00:55:23.174 --> 00:55:24.008
Step aside.

00:55:30.473 --> 00:55:31.474
Ms. Hong.

00:55:34.144 --> 00:55:36.813
I've left the door up here open.

00:55:38.022 --> 00:55:41.025
Take the elevator and go down one floor.

00:55:42.652 --> 00:55:43.695
This is…

00:55:45.572 --> 00:55:46.531
all I can do for you.

00:55:53.496 --> 00:55:54.497
Let's go.

00:55:58.001 --> 00:55:59.127
Right this way, sir.

00:55:59.836 --> 00:56:01.379
Please make your way inside.

00:56:04.007 --> 00:56:05.008
Just a moment.

00:56:05.967 --> 00:56:09.387
Shareholders holding a single share
need to wait on the side.

00:56:09.470 --> 00:56:11.472
Are you discriminating
against small shareholders?

00:56:11.556 --> 00:56:13.433
One is enough to make me a shareholder!

00:56:19.689 --> 00:56:20.607
Give me a second.

00:56:22.483 --> 00:56:24.194
Hello, Mr. So.

00:56:32.285 --> 00:56:33.119
Hey!

00:56:34.579 --> 00:56:36.247
Don't you know Division Manager So?

00:56:36.331 --> 00:56:38.625
Show him and his men in.

00:56:38.708 --> 00:56:40.793
They're clearly branch employees.

00:56:41.294 --> 00:56:42.170
Yes, sir.

00:56:42.253 --> 00:56:43.087
This way, sir.

00:56:43.171 --> 00:56:44.881
The time is now seven o'clock,

00:56:44.964 --> 00:56:46.925
so the shareholders' meeting
will commence.

00:57:10.865 --> 00:57:13.201
EXTRAORDINARY SHAREHOLDERS' MEETING
FEBRUARY 23, 1998

00:57:26.005 --> 00:57:26.839
All right.

00:57:29.300 --> 00:57:33.513
The Pirates' disruptors were stopped
at the front and hall entrances,

00:57:33.596 --> 00:57:34.597
with Albert included.

00:57:35.598 --> 00:57:36.849
Is that so?

00:57:39.519 --> 00:57:41.896
The special item on today's agenda,

00:57:41.980 --> 00:57:44.357
submitted by Yeouido Pirates,
the second-largest shareholder,

00:57:44.440 --> 00:57:46.150
is a motion to dismiss Chairman Kang.

00:57:47.151 --> 00:57:48.111
For the motion to pass,

00:57:48.194 --> 00:57:52.240
at least one-third of the issued shares
with voting rights must be present,

00:57:52.323 --> 00:57:56.119
and at least two-thirds of the represented
must vote in favor.

00:57:56.744 --> 00:57:57.870
Before we proceed--

00:57:57.954 --> 00:57:59.789
I vote in favor
of dismissing Chairman Kang!

00:58:00.665 --> 00:58:02.834
-I vote in favor!
-Reinstate the laid-off workers!

00:58:02.917 --> 00:58:04.627
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

00:58:04.711 --> 00:58:06.796
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

00:58:06.879 --> 00:58:08.464
-Dismiss him!
-Dismiss him!

00:58:08.548 --> 00:58:10.425
Reinstate the laid-off workers!

00:58:10.508 --> 00:58:11.676
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

00:58:11.759 --> 00:58:14.012
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

00:58:14.095 --> 00:58:15.638
-Dismiss him!
-Dismiss him!

00:58:21.185 --> 00:58:22.979
You see,

00:58:23.771 --> 00:58:27.483
I spent 26 years and 11 months at Hanmin.

00:58:28.818 --> 00:58:31.070
I may not have always been at my best,

00:58:31.154 --> 00:58:34.198
but I thought I was making
the best choices I could.

00:58:36.034 --> 00:58:38.661
In hindsight,
I see that I made one too many

00:58:39.746 --> 00:58:41.331
cowardly and shameful choices.

00:58:43.499 --> 00:58:46.336
As for what really happened
with the order error incident,

00:58:46.836 --> 00:58:48.338
I assume you already know.

00:58:49.797 --> 00:58:50.673
It's much too late,

00:58:51.257 --> 00:58:52.258
but I'd like to apologize.

00:58:56.220 --> 00:58:58.348
After Chairman Kang is dismissed,

00:58:58.431 --> 00:59:01.392
we plan to reinstate
laid-off employees in phases.

00:59:02.018 --> 00:59:04.103
How would you like to join us, Mr. So?

00:59:05.563 --> 00:59:07.940
It could be the best choice you can make.

00:59:17.742 --> 00:59:19.118
The blame for failed management

00:59:19.202 --> 00:59:21.746
rests squarely with senior leadership
and the owners.

00:59:21.829 --> 00:59:23.456
-Scapegoating the employees
-That…

00:59:23.539 --> 00:59:25.124
and laying them off is reprehensible!

00:59:25.208 --> 00:59:26.751
Reinstate the laid-off workers!

00:59:26.834 --> 00:59:28.503
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

00:59:28.586 --> 00:59:30.421
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

00:59:30.505 --> 00:59:31.798
-Dismiss him!
-Dismiss him!

00:59:31.881 --> 00:59:33.800
Reinstate the laid-off workers!

00:59:33.883 --> 00:59:35.093
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

00:59:35.176 --> 00:59:37.261
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

00:59:37.345 --> 00:59:40.598
Any disruptive behavior in the hall
will result in removal from the venue.

00:59:40.682 --> 00:59:42.558
-Reinstate us!
-Reinstate us!

00:59:42.642 --> 00:59:44.602
Dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom!

01:00:06.582 --> 01:00:09.669
Let's start with the vote on the motion
to dismiss Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

01:00:16.759 --> 01:00:19.387
At today's shareholders' meeting,
Yeouido Pirates announces

01:00:19.470 --> 01:00:22.390
its support for the motion to dismiss
Hanmin's Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

01:00:22.473 --> 01:00:25.435
Out of a total of
90 million issued shares of Hanmin,

01:00:25.518 --> 01:00:28.312
Yeouido Pirates has secured
a total of 31 million shares,

01:00:28.396 --> 01:00:30.440
including shares represented by proxy,

01:00:30.523 --> 01:00:34.110
thereby obtaining the support of more
than one-third of the outstanding shares.

01:00:40.366 --> 01:00:42.994
We will now proceed to a ballot vote.

01:00:44.537 --> 01:00:46.205
Shareholders who support the motion,

01:00:46.289 --> 01:00:48.416
please mark your ballots and submit them.

01:01:10.480 --> 01:01:11.856
IN FAVOR

01:01:11.939 --> 01:01:12.982
IN FAVOR

01:01:31.459 --> 01:01:33.961
The percentage of voting rights present

01:01:34.962 --> 01:01:37.465
cast in favor of
Chairman Kang Pil-beom's removal

01:01:37.965 --> 01:01:40.009
was 41.4%,

01:01:40.092 --> 01:01:42.637
and failed to meet the threshold
for a special resolution.

01:01:44.430 --> 01:01:47.934
Therefore, I officially declare
this motion defeated.

01:01:57.902 --> 01:01:59.779
How dare they try me?

01:02:03.491 --> 01:02:05.159
Thank you for your hard work.

01:02:05.827 --> 01:02:07.036
Well done.

01:02:07.620 --> 01:02:09.455
Until next time.

01:02:14.168 --> 01:02:15.378
Thank you for today.

01:02:43.447 --> 01:02:45.157
They got So Gyeong-dong too?

01:02:46.033 --> 01:02:47.952
When did he join their side?

01:02:48.911 --> 01:02:51.205
They all used to wait with bated breath,

01:02:51.289 --> 01:02:55.167
anxiously hanging on my every word!

01:02:55.251 --> 01:02:57.461
You still won, Father.

01:03:01.340 --> 01:03:02.258
Ms. Song.

01:03:02.842 --> 01:03:05.303
Prepare for our first
press conference of the year.

01:03:06.387 --> 01:03:07.638
Now is the time

01:03:08.139 --> 01:03:12.810
to announce Nora to the world
as the new face of Hanmin.

01:03:20.443 --> 01:03:23.154
YEOUIDO PIRATES' FAILED TAKEOVER OF HANMIN
HAVE THEY BECOME A SINKING SHIP?

01:03:23.237 --> 01:03:25.656
KANG PIL-BEOM GOING STRONG
WHERE IS HANMIN HEADED NOW?

01:03:26.240 --> 01:03:28.492
AFTER SECURING MANAGEMENT CONTROL,
PRESIDENT KANG NORA TAKES LEAD

01:03:28.576 --> 01:03:30.536
"…and members of the press, I'm--"

01:03:30.620 --> 01:03:31.621
1998, DAY OF NEW YEAR CONFERENCE

01:03:31.704 --> 01:03:35.124
"I'm Kang Nora, the president of Hanmin."

01:03:35.207 --> 01:03:39.337
"In light of the unfortunate developments
surrounding Hanmin…"

01:03:39.420 --> 01:03:41.589
Have you memorized
the press statement I gave you?

01:03:42.548 --> 01:03:44.175
Yes, almost.

01:03:44.884 --> 01:03:46.010
About 61%?

01:03:50.389 --> 01:03:51.265
Option one.

01:03:51.849 --> 01:03:54.143
A clean-cut, classic suit.

01:03:54.226 --> 01:03:57.855
It aims to deliver a message
about continuing our tradition and legacy.

01:03:59.065 --> 01:03:59.899
Option two.

01:03:59.982 --> 01:04:02.818
It reflects a youthful,
future-oriented image

01:04:02.902 --> 01:04:06.822
aimed at increasing brand awareness
among the younger age demographic.

01:04:13.079 --> 01:04:13.955
Hello?

01:04:30.262 --> 01:04:31.263
Who was that?

01:04:32.390 --> 01:04:35.101
Only a few people know your Korean number.

01:04:36.686 --> 01:04:37.520
It was my mom.

01:04:37.603 --> 01:04:39.814
She said I should make sure
I'm presentable.

01:04:44.610 --> 01:04:45.778
Be careful around the chairman.

01:04:47.571 --> 01:04:49.907
I'll be here ten minutes early
to escort you.

01:04:55.329 --> 01:04:57.873
I recommend the first option.

01:04:58.958 --> 01:04:59.834
Okay.

01:05:37.079 --> 01:05:38.914
KANG EUN-JOO

01:05:43.878 --> 01:05:45.087
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

01:05:48.215 --> 01:05:50.092
PRESIDENT KANG NORA'S
NEW YEAR PRESS CONFERENCE

01:06:04.106 --> 01:06:05.149
What are you doing?

01:06:06.859 --> 01:06:08.569
Oh, my outfit?

01:06:09.278 --> 01:06:11.864
I know you prepared several options,

01:06:11.947 --> 01:06:15.659
but is there a better outfit
to symbolize the past, present, and future

01:06:16.619 --> 01:06:19.080
than our uniform?

01:06:38.349 --> 01:06:41.602
Hello, I'm Kang Nora, the president
of Hanmin Investment &amp; Securities.

01:06:41.685 --> 01:06:42.937
Before I became president,

01:06:43.020 --> 01:06:47.316
I joined Hanmin on September 1, 1997,
as an entry-level employee,

01:06:47.399 --> 01:06:50.486
under my childhood name of Kang Eun-joo.

01:06:50.569 --> 01:06:54.573
Chairman Kang Pil-beom wished for me
to start at the bottom

01:06:54.657 --> 01:06:57.576
and learn alongside ordinary people.

01:06:57.660 --> 01:06:58.953
Well done, sir.

01:07:06.710 --> 01:07:08.546
That's also when I left home

01:07:08.629 --> 01:07:11.841
and moved into the Seoul City Dormitory
for Single Female Workers

01:07:11.924 --> 01:07:13.843
to live with roommates for three months.

01:07:16.303 --> 01:07:20.015
That was when I learned family is about
sharing meals, laughing together,

01:07:20.099 --> 01:07:21.517
and even arguing at times.

01:07:24.562 --> 01:07:28.691
I consider every Hanmin employee
a member of my family.

01:07:31.986 --> 01:07:33.863
For the sake of Hanmin

01:07:33.946 --> 01:07:36.282
and for the sake of the Hanmin family,

01:07:36.866 --> 01:07:40.452
I will exercise my shareholder rights
in support of Yeouido Pirates.

01:07:40.536 --> 01:07:42.413
What's this now?

01:08:29.543 --> 01:08:31.378
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

01:08:31.962 --> 01:08:33.672
They won't just stand by and watch.

01:08:33.756 --> 01:08:36.884
If it's all gone to hell,
let's take what's ours while we can.

01:08:36.967 --> 01:08:38.510
This is an urgent directive
from the chairman.

01:08:38.594 --> 01:08:40.721
How much cash do you have on hand?

01:08:40.804 --> 01:08:43.682
If Ms. Song, who knows too much
about the slush fund, is gone…

01:08:43.766 --> 01:08:45.434
He could avoid a guilty verdict?

01:08:45.517 --> 01:08:47.186
Chairman Kang is doing that on purpose.

01:08:47.269 --> 01:08:48.145
He knows I can't speak up.

01:08:48.229 --> 01:08:50.147
Stop being so stubborn.

01:08:50.231 --> 01:08:52.066
The defense had
also requested this witness.

01:08:52.149 --> 01:08:54.151
He is already in attendance
in the courtroom.

01:08:54.652 --> 01:08:56.528
Nora, come meet me right now.

01:08:56.612 --> 01:09:00.741
-What is it?
-Now, none of you can make it out alive.

01:09:00.824 --> 01:09:03.619
Thank you for all your hard work
over the years.

01:09:05.788 --> 01:09:10.793
Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim